cyclone.name: DOLORES
cyclone.current_location: about 265 miles SSE of Acapulco, Mexico
cyclone.trajectory: Tracking west-northwest parallel to the southern and southwestern coast of Mexico and expected to remain offshore, moving south of the Baja California Peninsula
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: Not forecast to make landfall (core remains offshore)

weather_observation.impacted_coast: Southern and southwestern coast of Mexico and offshore waters south of the Baja California Peninsula
weather_observation.wind: No significant tropical-storm-force winds expected at Port of Long Beach, CA.
weather_observation.other_hazards: Long-period swells generated by the cyclone could reach Southern California waters late in the week, producing higher surf and rip currents, but port operations are not expected to be directly disrupted.
